02/03/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Minister of Public Order Luan Rama vowed Saturday (1 March) that his country's policy of co-operation with international law enforcement structures would continue. 
Receiving a delegation of the US Justice Department's International Criminal Investigative Training Assistance Programme (ICITAP), Rama said Albanian police are grateful for the help that ICITAP has given. 
In turn, ICITAP praised Albania's role in curbing regional organised crime. 
(ATA - 01/03/03)
